Maryland Per Capita Personal Income Analysis

Executive Summary

This notebook provides a comprehensive exploratory data analysis of Maryland's Per Capita Personal Income data. The analysis examines income patterns across different dimensions including geography, time periods, and demographic factors.

Data Source: Maryland State Database
Database: Maryland
Table: PerCapitaPersonalIncome
Note: All income values are in U.S. dollars.

import os
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

import warnings

warnings.filterwarnings("ignore", message="pandas only supports SQLAlchemy connectable")

# Set plotting style
sns.set_palette("husl")
plt.rcParams['figure.dpi'] = 100

# Helper function to format large numbers
def format_currency(value):
    """Format currency values for better readability"""
    if pd.isna(value):
        return "N/A"
    if value >= 1_000_000_000:
        return f"${value/1_000_000_000:.2f}B"
    elif value >= 1_000_000:
        return f"${value/1_000_000:.2f}M"
    elif value >= 1_000:
        return f"${value/1_000:.2f}K"
    else:
        return f"${value:.2f}"

# Connect and load data from SQL
SQL_QUERY = """
SELECT *
FROM [Maryland].[dbo].[PerCapitaPersonalIncome]
"""

print(" Loading Maryland Per Capita Personal Income Data...\n")

try:
    conn = mssql_python.connect(SQL_CONNECTION_STRING)
    df = pd.read_sql(SQL_QUERY, conn)
    conn.close()
    
    print(f" Data loaded successfully: {len(df):,} rows  {len(df.columns)} columns")
    print(f" Columns: {', '.join(df.columns.tolist())}")
    
except Exception as e:
    print(f" Error loading data: {e}")
    raise

print("\n" + "="*80)

# Missing Values Analysis
print("Missing Values Analysis:\n")

missing_counts = df.isnull().sum()
missing_pct = (df.isnull().sum() / len(df)) * 100

missing_df = pd.DataFrame({
    'Column': df.columns,
    'Missing Count': missing_counts.values,
    'Missing %': missing_pct.values
}).sort_values('Missing Count', ascending=False)

print(missing_df.to_string(index=False))

print("\n" + "="*80)
print("\nMissing Data Summary:")
print(f"  Total columns with missing data: {(missing_counts > 0).sum()}")
print(f"  Total missing values: {missing_counts.sum():,}")
print(f"  Overall missing percentage: {(missing_counts.sum() / (df.shape[0] * df.shape[1]) * 100):.2f}%")

# Visualize missing data if any exists
if missing_counts.sum() > 0:
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))
    missing_data = missing_df[missing_df['Missing Count'] > 0]
    
    if len(missing_data) > 0:
        ax.barh(missing_data['Column'], missing_data['Missing %'], color='coral', edgecolor='darkred', alpha=0.8)
        ax.set_xlabel('Missing Percentage (%)', fontsize=12, fontweight='bold')
        ax.set_title('Missing Values by Column', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold', pad=15)
        ax.grid(axis='x', alpha=0.3, linestyle='--')
        
        # Add value labels
        for i, v in enumerate(missing_data['Missing %']):
            ax.text(v + 0.5, i, f'{v:.1f}%', va='center', fontsize=9, fontweight='bold')
        
        plt.tight_layout()
        plt.show()
else:
    print("\n No missing values detected in the dataset!")

print("\n" + "="*80)

# Descriptive Statistics for Numerical Variables (excluding temporal identifiers)
print("Descriptive Statistics - Numerical Variables:\n")
numerical_cols = df.select_dtypes(include=[np.number]).columns.tolist()

# Filter out temporal/identifier columns that shouldn't be analyzed statistically
columns_to_exclude = ['year', 'id', 'code', 'index']
numerical_cols_filtered = [col for col in numerical_cols if not any(excl in col.lower() for excl in columns_to_exclude)]

print(f"Analyzing {len(numerical_cols_filtered)} income measure columns (excluding temporal identifiers like Year)\n")

if len(numerical_cols_filtered) > 0:
    desc_stats = df[numerical_cols_filtered].describe()
    print(desc_stats.to_string())
    
    print("\n" + "="*80)
    print("\n **Key Insights:**")
    print(f"    Average income range: ${desc_stats.loc['mean'].min():,.0f} to ${desc_stats.loc['mean'].max():,.0f}")
    print(f"    Highest maximum income: ${desc_stats.loc['max'].max():,.0f} ({desc_stats.loc['max'].idxmax()})")
    print(f"    Income variability: Standard deviations range from ${desc_stats.loc['std'].min():,.0f} to ${desc_stats.loc['std'].max():,.0f}")
    
    print("\n" + "="*80)
    print("\nAdditional Statistics:\n")
    
    for col in numerical_cols_filtered:

# Detailed categorical analysis with visualizations
categorical_cols = df.select_dtypes(include=['object']).columns.tolist()

if categorical_cols:
    for col in categorical_cols:
        unique_count = df[col].nunique()
        
        print(f"\n{'='*80}")
        print(f"Categorical Analysis: {col.upper().replace('_', ' ')}")
        print(f"{'='*80}\n")
        
        print(f"  Unique Values: {unique_count:,}")
        print(f"  Most Common: {df[col].mode().iloc[0] if len(df[col].mode()) > 0 else 'N/A'}")
        print(f"  Least Common: {df[col].value_counts().idxmin() if len(df[col].value_counts()) > 0 else 'N/A'}")
        
        value_counts = df[col].value_counts()
        
        # Display top values
        display_limit = min(15, unique_count)
        print(f"\n  Top {display_limit} Values:")
        for i, (val, count) in enumerate(value_counts.head(display_limit).items(), 1):
            pct = (count / len(df)) * 100
            print(f"    {i:2d}. {val}: {count:,} ({pct:.1f}%)")
        
        # Visualize if reasonable number of categories
        if unique_count <= 20:
            plt.figure(figsize=(12, max(6, unique_count * 0.4)))
            bars = plt.barh(range(len(value_counts)), value_counts.values, color='teal', edgecolor='darkslategray', linewidth=1.5)

            plt.xlabel('Count', fontsize=12, fontweight='bold')
            plt.title(f'Distribution of {col.replace("_", " ").title()}', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold', pad=20)
            
            # Add value labels
            for i, bar in enumerate(bars):
                width = bar.get_width()
                plt.text(width, bar.get_y() + bar.get_height()/2, f'{int(width):,}',
                        ha='left', va='center', fontsize=9, fontweight='bold')
            
            plt.grid(axis='x', alpha=0.3, linestyle='--')
            plt.tight_layout()
            plt.show()
        else:
            # Bar plot for top 15

if year_cols and numerical_cols_filtered:
    year_col = year_cols[0]
    
    print(f"Analyzing: {year_col} with {len(numerical_cols_filtered)} county income columns")
    print("\n" + "="*80)
    print("\nDescriptive Statistics by Year (across all counties):\n")
    
    # Melt the data to get all income values by year
    melted_df = df.melt(id_vars=[year_col], value_vars=numerical_cols_filtered, 
                        var_name='County', value_name='Income')
    
    # Calculate statistics for each year
    yearly_stats = melted_df.groupby(year_col)['Income'].agg([
        ('Count', 'count'),
        ('Mean', 'mean'),
        ('Median', 'median'),
        ('Std Dev', 'std'),
        ('Min', 'min'),
        ('Max', 'max'),
        ('Range', lambda x: x.max() - x.min()),
        ('25th Pct', lambda x: x.quantile(0.25)),
        ('75th Pct', lambda x: x.quantile(0.75)),
        ('IQR', lambda x: x.quantile(0.75) - x.quantile(0.25))
    ]).round(2)
    
    print(yearly_stats.to_string())

    print(f"    Standard deviation trend: {'increasing' if yearly_stats['Std Dev'].iloc[-1] > yearly_stats['Std Dev'].iloc[0] else 'decreasing'} (disparity {'growing' if yearly_stats['Std Dev'].iloc[-1] > yearly_stats['Std Dev'].iloc[0] else 'narrowing'})")

# Transform data from wide format to long format for geographic analysis
# In wide format: Year | County1 | County2 | ... | CountyN

if year_col and len(numerical_cols_filtered) > 0:
    print(f"Analyzing: {len(numerical_cols_filtered)} counties over time")
    print(f"Year column: {year_col}")
    print(f"Counties: {', '.join(numerical_cols_filtered[:5])}... (and {len(numerical_cols_filtered)-5} more)" if len(numerical_cols_filtered) > 5 else f"Counties: {', '.join(numerical_cols_filtered)}")
    print("\n" + "="*80)
    
    # Create pivot table from existing wide format (already pivoted)
    pivot_data = df.set_index(year_col)[numerical_cols_filtered].T

    avg_income = pivot_data.mean(axis=1).sort_values(ascending=False)
    
    for i, (county, avg) in enumerate(avg_income.head(5).items(), 1):
        consistency = pivot_data.loc[county].std()
        print(f"  {i}. {county}")
        print(f"     Average Income: {format_currency(avg)}")
        print(f"     Std Dev: {format_currency(consistency)} (volatility)")
        print(f"     Range: {format_currency(pivot_data.loc[county].min())} to {format_currency(pivot_data.loc[county].max())}")
    
    print("\n" + "-"*80)
    print("\nTop 5 Poorest Counties (by average across all years):\n")
    
    for i, (county, avg) in enumerate(avg_income.tail(5).iloc[::-1].items(), 1):
        consistency = pivot_data.loc[county].std()
        print(f"  {i}. {county}")
        print(f"     Average Income: {format_currency(avg)}")
        print(f"     Std Dev: {format_currency(consistency)} (volatility)")
        print(f"     Range: {format_currency(pivot_data.loc[county].min())} to {format_currency(pivot_data.loc[county].max())}")

if year_col and len(numerical_cols_filtered) > 0:
    print("County Rankings and Income Tier Analysis:\n")
    print("="*80)
    
    # Transform wide format to get pivot data (counties as rows, years as columns)
    pivot_data = df.set_index(year_col)[numerical_cols_filtered].T
    
    # Calculate state average (Maryland)
    maryland_cols = [col for col in numerical_cols_filtered if 'maryland' in col.lower() and 'county' not in col.lower()]
    if len(maryland_cols) > 0:
        state_avg = df.set_index(year_col)[maryland_cols[0]]
    else:
        state_avg = pivot_data.mean(axis=0)
    
    # Rankings for each year
    rankings = pivot_data.rank(ascending=False, axis=0)
    
    print("\nCounty Rankings (Latest Year):\n")
    latest_year = pivot_data.columns[-1]
    latest_rankings = pivot_data[latest_year].sort_values(ascending=False)
    
    for rank, (county, income) in enumerate(latest_rankings.items(), 1):
        vs_state = income - state_avg[latest_year]
        vs_state_pct = (vs_state / state_avg[latest_year]) * 100
        status = "" if vs_state > 0 else ""
        print(f"  {rank:2d}. {county:<35} {format_currency(income):>12} "
              f"{status} {format_currency(abs(vs_state)):>10} ({vs_state_pct:+.1f}%)")
    
    # Counties above/below state average
    print("\n" + "="*80)
    print("\nCounties Above/Below State Average by Year:\n")
    
    for year in pivot_data.columns:
        above_state = (pivot_data[year] > state_avg[year]).sum()
        below_state = (pivot_data[year] < state_avg[year]).sum()
        at_state = (pivot_data[year] == state_avg[year]).sum()
        
        print(f"  {year}: Above={above_state}, Below={below_state}, At={at_state} "
              f"(State Avg: {format_currency(state_avg[year])})")
    
    # Income Tiers
    print("\n" + "="*80)
    print("\nIncome Tier Classification (Latest Year):\n")
    
    # Calculate tertiles
    q33 = pivot_data[latest_year].quantile(0.33)
    q67 = pivot_data[latest_year].quantile(0.67)
    
    high_tier = pivot_data[pivot_data[latest_year] >= q67][latest_year]
    medium_tier = pivot_data[(pivot_data[latest_year] >= q33) & 
                             (pivot_data[latest_year] < q67)][latest_year]
    low_tier = pivot_data[pivot_data[latest_year] < q33][latest_year]
    
    print(f"High Income Tier ( {format_currency(q67)}):")
    print(f"  Counties: {len(high_tier)}")
    for county, income in high_tier.sort_values(ascending=False).items():
        print(f"     {county}: {format_currency(income)}")
    
    print(f"\nMedium Income Tier ({format_currency(q33)} - {format_currency(q67)}):")
    print(f"  Counties: {len(medium_tier)}")
    for county, income in medium_tier.sort_values(ascending=False).items():
        print(f"     {county}: {format_currency(income)}")
    
    print(f"\nLow Income Tier (< {format_currency(q33)}):")
    print(f"  Counties: {len(low_tier)}")
    for county, income in low_tier.sort_values(ascending=False).items():
        print(f"     {county}: {format_currency(income)}")
    
    # Visualizations
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(16, 12))
    
    # Ranking changes over time for selected counties
    selected_counties = latest_rankings.head(3).index.tolist() + latest_rankings.tail(3).index.tolist()
    for county in selected_counties:

                       marker='o', linewidth=2, markersize=6, label=county)
    
    axes[0, 0].set_title('County Rankings Over Time (Top 3 & Bottom 3)',

    axes[0, 0].grid(True, alpha=0.3, linestyle='--')
    
    # Counties above vs below state average

        'Below': [(pivot_data[year] < state_avg[year]).sum() for year in pivot_data.columns]
    }, index=pivot_data.columns)
    
    above_below_data.plot(kind='bar', ax=axes[0, 1], color=['green', 'red'],

    axes[0, 1].set_title('Counties Above/Below State Average Over Time',

if year_col and len(numerical_cols_filtered) > 0:
    print("Income Inequality and Disparity Analysis:\n")
    print("="*80)
    
    # Transform wide format to get pivot data (counties as rows, years as columns)
    pivot_data = df.set_index(year_col)[numerical_cols_filtered].T
    
    # Calculate inequality metrics for each year
    inequality_metrics = pd.DataFrame({
        'Mean': pivot_data.mean(axis=0),
        'Std Dev': pivot_data.std(axis=0),
        'CV': (pivot_data.std(axis=0) / pivot_data.mean(axis=0)) * 100,
        'Min': pivot_data.min(axis=0),
        'Max': pivot_data.max(axis=0),
        'Range': pivot_data.max(axis=0) - pivot_data.min(axis=0),
        'Max/Min Ratio': pivot_data.max(axis=0) / pivot_data.min(axis=0),
        'Gini Approx': None  # Placeholder for Gini coefficient
    })
    
    # Calculate approximate Gini coefficient for each year
    for year in pivot_data.columns:
        values = pivot_data[year].dropna().sort_values().values
        n = len(values)
        if n > 0:
            index = np.arange(1, n + 1)
            gini = ((2 * index - n - 1) * values).sum() / (n * values.sum())
            inequality_metrics.loc[year, 'Gini Approx'] = gini
    
    print("\nInequality Metrics by Year:\n")
    print(inequality_metrics.to_string())
    
    print("\n" + "="*80)
    print("\nCoefficient of Variation (CV) Analysis:")
    print(f"  (CV measures relative dispersion - higher values = more inequality)\n")
    
    for year, cv in inequality_metrics['CV'].items():
        trend = ""
        if year != inequality_metrics.index[0]:
            prev_year = inequality_metrics.index[inequality_metrics.index.get_loc(year) - 1]
            change = cv - inequality_metrics.loc[prev_year, 'CV']
            trend = f" ({'' if change > 0 else ''} {abs(change):.2f})"
        print(f"  {year}: {cv:.2f}%{trend}")
    
    print("\n" + "="*80)
    print("\nMax/Min Income Ratio Analysis:")
    print(f"  (How many times larger is the richest county vs. poorest)\n")
    
    for year, ratio in inequality_metrics['Max/Min Ratio'].items():
        max_county = pivot_data[year].idxmax()
        min_county = pivot_data[year].idxmin()
        print(f"  {year}: {ratio:.2f}x ({max_county} vs {min_county})")
    
    # Convergence/Divergence Analysis
    print("\n" + "="*80)
    print("\nConvergence/Divergence Analysis:\n")
    
    first_year = pivot_data.columns[0]
    last_year = pivot_data.columns[-1]
    
    cv_change = inequality_metrics.loc[last_year, 'CV'] - inequality_metrics.loc[first_year, 'CV']
    ratio_change = inequality_metrics.loc[last_year, 'Max/Min Ratio'] - \
                   inequality_metrics.loc[first_year, 'Max/Min Ratio']
    
    if cv_change > 0:
        print(f"    DIVERGENCE DETECTED")
        print(f"     Income inequality has INCREASED over time")
    else:
        print(f"    CONVERGENCE DETECTED")
        print(f"     Income inequality has DECREASED over time")
    
    print(f"\n  Coefficient of Variation:")
    print(f"     {first_year}: {inequality_metrics.loc[first_year, 'CV']:.2f}%")
    print(f"     {last_year}: {inequality_metrics.loc[last_year, 'CV']:.2f}%")
    print(f"     Change: {cv_change:+.2f}%")
    
    print(f"\n  Max/Min Ratio:")
    print(f"     {first_year}: {inequality_metrics.loc[first_year, 'Max/Min Ratio']:.2f}x")
    print(f"     {last_year}: {inequality_metrics.loc[last_year, 'Max/Min Ratio']:.2f}x")
    print(f"     Change: {ratio_change:+.2f}x")
    
    # Visualizations
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(16, 12))
    
    # Coefficient of Variation over time
    axes[0, 0].plot(inequality_metrics.index, inequality_metrics['CV'], 
                   marker='o', linewidth=2.5, markersize=8, color='darkred')
    axes[0, 0].set_title('Coefficient of Variation Over Time', 
                        fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')
    axes[0, 0].set_xlabel('Year', fontsize=11, fontweight='bold')
    axes[0, 0].set_ylabel('CV (%)', fontsize=11, fontweight='bold')
    axes[0, 0].grid(True, alpha=0.3, linestyle='--')
    axes[0, 0].fill_between(inequality_metrics.index, inequality_metrics['CV'], 
                           alpha=0.3, color='red')
    
    # Max/Min Ratio over time
    axes[0, 1].plot(inequality_metrics.index, inequality_metrics['Max/Min Ratio'], 
                   marker='s', linewidth=2.5, markersize=8, color='darkblue')
    axes[0, 1].set_title('Income Ratio (Max/Min) Over Time', 
                        fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')
    axes[0, 1].set_xlabel('Year', fontsize=11, fontweight='bold')
    axes[0, 1].set_ylabel('Ratio (times)', fontsize=11, fontweight='bold')
    axes[0, 1].grid(True, alpha=0.3, linestyle='--')
    
    # Range over time
    axes[1, 0].plot(inequality_metrics.index, inequality_metrics['Range'], 
                   marker='d', linewidth=2.5, markersize=8, color='purple')
    axes[1, 0].set_title('Income Range (Max - Min) Over Time',

    axes[1, 0].set_xlabel('Year', fontsize=11, fontweight='bold')

    axes[1, 0].grid(True, alpha=0.3, linestyle='--')

    print(f"   Fastest Growing County: {growth_rates.idxmax()} ({growth_rates.max():.2f}%)")

    print("\n COUNTY RANKINGS:")
    latest_rankings = pivot_data[last_year].sort_values(ascending=False)
    print(f"  Top 3 Wealthiest Counties ({last_year}):")
    for i, (county, income) in enumerate(latest_rankings.head(3).items(), 1):

    print(f"\n  Bottom 3 Counties ({last_year}):")
    for i, (county, income) in enumerate(latest_rankings.tail(3).iloc[::-1].items(), 1):
        print(f"    {i}. {county}: {format_currency(income)}")
    
    print("\n INCOME INEQUALITY:")

    cv_last = (pivot_data[last_year].std() / pivot_data[last_year].mean()) * 100
    cv_change = cv_last - cv_first
